Hi Lindsay,

Is this issue specific to the Windows CRAN checks?

This Windows-specific error was also affecting several Bioconductor 
packages until recently but has been addressed in the latest version of 
Rhtslib (v 1.15.6). What version of Rhtslib are they using for the CRAN 
checks? They need to make sure to use the version that belongs to BioC 3.9:

 ? http://bioconductor.org/packages/3.9/Rhtslib

which is the version that is known to work with R 3.6.0.

BTW have you considered submitting your package to Bioconductor? We 
typically don't provide support for CRAN packages even if they depend on 
other Bioconductor packages. In other (cruder) words, by submitting to 
CRAN, you're on your own.

Cheers,

H.


